# 2p_damage_numbers — HOST. M6 P04.
#
# Pulse Rifle is hitscan, fires a fixed 12 dmg/hit (no crit/falloff
# variance), and is the cleanest weapon to assert "the host fired 3
# shots → 3 hits → 3 NORMAL-tier damage-number spawns on host AND
# client". Asserts in the runner verify the wire round-trip — same
# numeric value spawned from both sides via mech_apply_damage on the
# host and client_handle_hit_event on the client (per spec §3.1).
#
# Host fires; client peer stays passive. Both processes log
# `dmgnum spawn ... dmg=12 tier=1` lines (one set on the host's UI
# client via HIT_EVENT loopback, one set on the remote client via
# the same broadcast). Tier 1 = DMG_TIER_NORMAL per
# src/particle.c::dmg_tier_for(uint8_t).

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_damage_numbers_host
network host 24091
name HostA
# Use aurora — outdoor map with a long central flat-floor section
# (free of foundry's parallax-noise / slipstream's basement walls)
# so the host's hitscan ray has unobstructed line-of-sight to the
# client peer 200 px away.
map aurora

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard

# Aurora floor at row 86 → world y = 86*32 = 2752; pelvis 40 above
# feet (36 px feet_below + 4 clearance) = 2712. Mid-map x cols 50–73
# is clear of both mountain peaks (cols 2–10 / W-10..W-2) and central
# pit (cols 74–86), so a 200 px gap puts both mechs on flat ground
# with no terrain between them.
spawn_at 1600 2712
peer_spawn 1 1800 2712

# Aim at the client peer's chest. Slight upward bias (screen-y −10
# from pelvis) places the ray on the torso, not the head.
aim 1800 2702

at 130 shot pre_match

# Three Pulse Rifle taps at 60-tick intervals (1 s apart) so each
# fire has cleared its cooldown. Each tap = one hitscan ray = one
# 12-dmg hit on mech 1's chest = one NORMAL-tier damage-number spawn.
at 200 tap fire
at 260 tap fire
at 320 tap fire

at 360 shot post_3_hits
at 420 end
